Mellon Bank Corp said a shareholderfiled a class action suit in Philadelphia in light of theprecipitous decline in Mellon's stock on the New York StockExchange.    Mellon's stock fell 3-1/2 to 40-7/8 today after plunging6-1/4 yesterday after the bank holding company reported itsfirst loss in its 118 years, according to the shareholder, JohnPaul Decker.    Yesterday, the company said it expected to report a firstquarter loss of between 55 mln and 65 mln dlrs and itsintention to reduce the quarterly dividend.    The shareholder charges that Mellon and its senior officersfailed to disclose the company's true financial conditionduring the class period, between February 1, 1985 andApril 2, 1987     Mellon said it had no comment because it had not yet seenthe suit. Reuter&#3;